The Details
•Handcrafted using sterling silver 
•The charms measure 3/4" x 1/4"

The Process
Hand stamping is a very different process than traditional engraving. Hand stamping is done entirely by hand, with a hammer and steel stamp. The stamps have letters or designs carved on the end and each is individually stamped into the metal with a hammer. Every item is carefully handcrafted, so certain variations are to be expected. This adds to the one of a kind nature and overall quality of each piece I create.

results.title: Live, Laugh, Loathe 4 inch Embroidery Hoop Wall and Desk Art
results.description:
Live, Laugh, Loathe 4 inch Embroidery Hoop Wall and Desk Art

Embroidery OG will ship orders 3-5 days after the order is placed. Orders with added lettering will ship within 2 weeks. Custom orders ship within 3-4 weeks (custom orders include options such as fonts, colors, sizes, etc. Custom orders also receive a picture of the pattern before embroidery starts so I can make sure it’s exactly the way you want it).

All embroidery done in hoops is backed with felt backing to help maintain the integrity of the stitches and life of the piece. Orders will be wrapped in tissue paper and padded in their box for their journey to you. 

Embroidery OG was born out of a need for a mom to have a creative outlet that didn’t involve the children. Nothing takes away stress quite like stabbing something a thousand times does (even if it is just a needle). Now I get to share the weird things I make with others who can enjoy them.

results.title: Easter Rainbow Egg hanging ornament
results.description:
This Easter Rainbow Egg hanging ornament makes a perfect spring gift.

A beautiful bright hanging Easter decoration with a yellow heart painted on the reverse and a bright yellow ribbon for hanging it up, it would be a lovely surprise for friends and family, or to provide the finishing touch for those special little spaces in your home.

Every piece is one of a kind with a fresh hand-painted multicoloured design on both sides. Each one is cut out from a slice of white earthenware clay, given a little wire hook, dried, fired in a potter's kiln, then dipped in glaze and hand painted with professional ceramic colours to fix the designs in the final firing.
